Los Angeles Street Los Angeles, CA 90012 GURARDADO DE ZELAYA LEONOR FILE: A42785993 2149 CASTLE PL DATE: August 18, 1998 POMONA, CA 91767 IMPORTANT: Please disregard this notice if your fingerprints were taken anytime after January 13, 1998 or if you have already been naturalized and have received your naturalization certificate. To continue processing of your application Form N-400, INS must send your fingerprints to the Federal Bureau of Investigation for a criminal history check. You have been scheduled to be fingerprinted at the location listed below: OFFICE Application Support Center LOCATION 10050 Magnolia Avenue Riverside, CA 92507 DATE AND HOUR September 10, 1998 Thursday 9:00AM ASK FOR: Fingerprinting Office REASON FOR Initial processing of your fingerprints. APPOINTMENT: The period of validity for your fingerprint check has expired. Your fingerprints have been rejected by the FBI on: BRING WITH YOU: THIS LETTER, your Alien Registration Card (if applicable), and photo identification such as passport, valid driver's license, national ID, military ID, State-issued photo ID, or other INS issued photo ID. If you do not bring this letter and proper photo identification, you will not be permitted to have your fingerprints taken. Please take note that the staff at the Application Support Center will not be able to answer any questions about the status of your application. Failure to appear may result in the denial of your application, I CAN NOT APPEAR FOR THIS APPOINTMENT BECAUSE: Sincerely, Richard K. Rogers SIGNATURE OF APPLICANT: DATE: District Director Form G-56
